description:
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Research Nurse - Band 6&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are looking for a dynamic research nurse to join our friendly team. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Based within the Royal United Hospitals Bath NHS FT, the internationally renowned Royal National Hospital for Rheumatic Diseases is a specialist hospital with an international reputation for research and services in Rheumatology, Chronic Pain and Fatigue management.  &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The post holder will work within a small but vibrant team of research nurses, clinical trials officers and administrators who work together with multidisciplinary colleagues to deliver both non-commercial and commercially funded research projects. The friendly team supports a rolling portfolio of circa 30 rheumatology projects with annual recruitment of 300 patients. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The successful applicant will work closely with our consultant colleagues to plan and deliver studies to time and target. The main sub-specialties are Ankylosing Spondylitis, Connective Tissue Diseases, Psoriatic Arthritis and Rheumatoid Arthritis.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Studies range from in-house registries and biobanks, studies to evaluate new technology such as Smartphone app’s, commerically funded drug studies and more recently the addition of Public Health England COVID studies.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The successful applicant will oversee their own portfolio of studies, key responsibilities include: recruitment, coordinating patient visits alongside pharmacy, radiology and other support services, accurate data collection and effective communication with patients, multi-disciplinary team members and commercial sponsors.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are looking for a personable candidate who prides themselves on their attention to detail, flexibility &amp; organisational skills. Previous experience in research and / or rheumatology is desirable but not essential&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interviews will be carried out virtually via Teams / telephone&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further information please contact: Debbie Delgado, Lead Research Nurse Tel: 01225 821801&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
